headline: Hoka Maker’s Stock Is the S&P 500’s Biggest Loser. Wall Street Sees Better Days Ahead.
summary: Shares of  Deckers Outdoor  the worst performer in the  this year through Tuesday, may be close to hitting bottom after a slide of more than 40%.  While investors are worried about how badly President Donald Trump’s tariffs will hurt earnings, the stock’s valuation compared with shares of other footwear companies, and slowing sales growth, analysts see reason for optimism.  Deckers makes both Hoka running shoes and UGG boots.
